posts.name: Justin Tsai
posts.cooked: I’m using SysID to test my robot, but I’m unable to move it.  Everything seems to be fine electrically, and the SysID code is deploying into the RoboRIO, but the CanSpark motor controllers are staying solid blue color, not red or green like it would be if it was running properly.  If anyone has and idea on what the problem is, can you please reply?  Thank you.

posts.name: Cameron Williams
posts.cooked: My team faced this problem too. We fixed it by making sure we had the most current version of sysid. Do you have the most up to date version of sysid?

posts.name: Justin Tsai
posts.cooked: I have SysID 2023v2.1, is that the newest version?

posts.name: Tyler Veness
posts.cooked: 2023.3.1 will be released soon, but you can try one of the artifacts from Make integration test assertions more informative (#476) · wpilibsuite/sysid@652060e · GitHub in the meantime. We fixed some NetworkTables connection issues.

link_counts.title: Make integration test assertions more informative (#476) · wpilibsuite/sysid@652060e · GitHub

posts.name: Justin Tsai
posts.cooked: Thank you so much, I was able to run my motors properly.  But I have to reboot the app to make it work, but thank you so much for the suggestion.

posts.name: Tyler Veness
posts.cooked:
JustinTime:

I have to reboot the app to make it work

Sounds like this issue: Using sysid for two separate deployments always fails w/ SysIdWrongMechanism=true · Issue #469 · wpilibsuite/sysid · GitHub
